A '''Mobility kill''' or (M-kill) refers to damage inflicted by a weapon on a vehicle that immobizes it - but does not destroy the vehicle totally, and leaves the vehicle able to use its weapons.

Typically this term is used to refer to [[tank]]s and other armoured vechicles that have their engines, tracks or running gear damaged. 

